curacy and performance. If a tool is not properly calibrated or its load is incorrectly defined, recalibration or load identification should be performed. 3. Mechanical and Environmental Checks: Inspect Tooling and Equipment: Verify that all tools and process equipment attached to the robot arms are securely fastened and rigid. Check for Mechanical Play/Wear: Inconsistent path accuracy can stem from damaged bearings, gearboxes, or mechanical joints. These components should be inspected and replaced if faulty. Environmental Factors: Consider external interference, loose connections, or thermal phenomena as potential causes for inconsistent behavior. Environmental conditions like ambient temperature can affect robot performance. By diligently addressing these aspects during robot installation and throughout its operational life, manufacturers and integrators can maximize robot accuracy, performance, and reliability.",
