[SEARCH] Resolved result: '[\n  {\n    "Document Name": "ABB_IRC5_Operating_Troubleshooting_Manual \\u2014 Page 41",\n    "Full Text": "If you are experiencing no voltage in the service outlet on your control module, particularly with an ABB IRC5 Control Module, several issues could be the cause. This problem means that external service equipment connected to the outlet will not function.\\n\\nHere are the probable causes, listed in order of likelihood, and recommended actions:\\n*   **Tripped Circuit Breaker (F5)** Ensure the circuit breaker within the Control Module has not tripped. Also, verify that any equipment connected to the service outlet is not drawing excessive power, which could cause the breaker to trip.\\n*   **Tripped Earth Fault Protection (F4)** Check if the earth fault protection has tripped. Make sure that any equipment plugged into the service outlet is not causing current to leak to the ground, which would activate this protection.\\n*   **Mains Power Supply Loss** Confirm that the power supply to the robot system meets specifications. You may need to refer to your plant documentation for the correct voltage values.\\n*   **Incorrectly Connected Transformers** Verify that the transformer supplying the outlet is correctly connected, ensuring that both input and output voltages align with specifications. Again, consult your plant documentation for the correct voltage values.\\n\\nThe troubleshooting steps also advise checking the main switch, ensuring the system is supplied with power using a voltmeter to measure incoming mains voltage, and checking the main transformer connection for correct voltage matching. If the main power supply is correct but other indicators (like LEDs) are off, the Drive Module power supply might need to be replaced.",\n    "Page Number": "",\n    "URL": "projects/338431745290/locations/global/collections/default_collection/dataStores/linamar-vector-bootcamp/branches/0/documents/abb-irc5-operating-troubleshooting-manual-p