    "excerpt": "The `Break` instruction is primarily used for debugging purposes. When encountered, it immediately halts program execution and stops robot movement, allowing the programmer to analyze variables and program states. After a `Break` instruction, program execution can typically be restarted from the very next instruction. It does not wait for the robot to reach its programmed destination before stopping.",
