    "url": "projects/338431745290/locations/global/collections/default_collection/dataStores/linamar-vector-bootcamp/branches/0/documents/abb-technical-reference-manual-p34",
    "excerpt": "The `Stop` instruction is used to temporarily pause program execution. Unlike `Break`, the robot will complete any ongoing movements and reach a standstill before the program truly stops. Program execution can then be restarted from the instruction immediately following the `Stop` command. It can be configured to stop only the program in the current task or, with the `AllMoveTasks` switch, stop programs in all normal tasks. The `Stop` instruction is intended for temporary pauses, allowing for a controlled resumption of the program.",
