    "excerpt": "The `EXIT` instruction is used for the permanent termination of program execution, typically in response to fatal errors. When `EXIT` is executed, the program pointer is removed, meaning the program cannot be restarted from its previous position. To continue operation after an `EXIT` instruction, the program must be restarted from the first instruction of the main routine, effectively performing a full reset. This makes `EXIT` a much more severe termination than `Stop` or `Break`.",
