To manually release the brakes on an IRB 8700, use the internal brake release unit, which has individual buttons for each axis.

**DANGER**: The robot axes can move very quickly and unpredictably when the holding brakes are released. Ensure no personnel are near or beneath the robot arm before proceeding. If the robot is a larger model, an overhead crane or similar equipment might be required to manage the arm's movement.

**Procedure:**
1.  Locate the internal brake release unit inside a cover on the robot.
2.  The unit has buttons numbered according to the robot's axes.
3.  Press the corresponding button for the specific axis whose holding brake you wish to release.
4.  The brake will re-engage as soon as the button is released.

If the robot is not connected to the controller, external power must be supplied to the R1.MP connectors to enable the brake release buttons.

<details>
<summary>Found in search:</summary>
<p>To manually release the brakes on an ABB IRB 8700 robot, you will need to use the internal brake release unit, which contains individual buttons for each axis.</p>
<p><strong>Important Safety Precautions:</strong>
*   <strong>DANGER:</strong> The robot axes can move very quickly and unpredictably when the holding brakes are released. Ensure no personnel are near or beneath the robot arm before proceeding.
*   If the robot is on a larger model, an overhead crane or similar equipment might be required to manage the arm's movement after brake release.
*   Before releasing the brakes, confirm that the robot's weight will not worsen any existing injury, especially if someone is trapped.
*   If the robot is not connected to the controller, external power must be supplied to the R1.MP connectors to enable the brake release buttons. The IRB 8700 has two R1.MP connectors: R1.MP-A and R1.MP-B. Supplying power to the incorrect pin can cause all brakes to release simultaneously. For axes 1, 2, and 3, supply 0V to pin 12 of R1.MP-A and 24V to pin 11 of R1.MP-B.</p>
<p><strong>Procedure for Manually Releasing the Brakes:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Locate the Internal Brake Release Unit:</strong> This unit is situated inside a cover on the robot.</li>
<li><strong>Access the Buttons:</strong> The internal brake release unit has buttons numbered according to the robot's axes.</li>
<li><strong>Release the Brake:</strong> Press the corresponding button on the internal brake release unit for the specific robot axis whose holding brake you wish to release.</li>
<li><strong>Re-engage the Brake:</strong> The brake will re-engage as soon as you release the button.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Note on Maintenance:</strong>
If service work has been performed inside the SMB recess involving the removal and refitting of the brake release unit, ensure that the push-buttons are not jammed. A jammed button with power on will release the affected motor brake, posing a significant safety risk. Always verify that the buttons move freely before powering on the robot after such maintenance.</p>
<p><em>Reference: ABB_IRB8700_Product_Manual.pdf</em></p>
